This paper deals with semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves mapping natural language sentences to formal representations of their meaning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for ontology learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) aspects, as it involves capturing and representing semantic meaning of text, which can be used for information retrieval and database applications.
